---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import SiteNav from "../components/SiteNav.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
import "../styles/manual.css";
import "../styles/force-glyphs.css";

// A second, playful homepage — "field-ui, explained like you're 5". Same engine and the same
// home structure (the shared <field-root>, the chapter/stage layout, and the HomeRuntime +
// StageFieldOverlay wiring at the bottom), but a story-first narrative instead of the manual.
//
// Every stage here is a REAL body in the shared field — the demos use the same data-* contract
// as the main home page (data-body / data-drag / data-feedback / data-threads / data-preset), so
// nothing is faked: the dots actually swim, and the field-line overlay traces the true paths.
// The runtime only activates on pages with `.manual-shell`, which this page provides.
---

<Base
  title="field-ui — explained like you're 5"
  description="A webpage you can play with, that plays back. field-ui sprinkles invisible magnets onto a page: a word can call the dots in, a button can push them away, and when matter piles up the word notices and grows. Things bend the field; the field bends them back — and the dots are just the easiest thing to see."
>
  <SiteNav />
  <div class="manual-shell">
    <header class="manual-hero" id="top">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="kicker">field-ui · explained like you're 5</p>
        <h1>A webpage you can <span class="accent">play with</span> — that plays
          back.</h1>
        <p class="standfirst">
          You know how a magnet can push and pull without touching anything?
          field-ui sprinkles invisible magnets onto a webpage. A word can say
          “come here!” and the little floating dots all swim toward it. A button
          can say “stay back!” and they scoot away. Some things spin the dots in
          circles; some gobble them up like a tiny black hole.
        </p>
        <p class="thesis">
          <strong>And the magic part — it goes both ways.</strong> Pile enough dots
          on a word and the word notices: it grows bigger, bolder, glowier. Things
          bend the invisible field, and the field bends them back.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/docs">Read the docs →</a>
          <a class="btn" href="/lab">Open the Lab →</a>
          <a class="btn" href="/">See the grown-up version →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-flow">
          <button
            id="flowToggle"
            class="flow-toggle"
            type="button"
            aria-pressed="false"
          >
            <span class="ft-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Make the dots follow you
          </button>
          <span class="flow-hint"
            >move your cursor — the whole field leans toward it</span
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <nav class="chapter-rail" aria-label="Chapters">
      <a href="#ch-magnets" data-ch="ch-magnets"
        ><span class="cr-no">1</span><span class="cr-label">Magnets</span></a
      >
      <a href="#ch-things" data-ch="ch-things"
        ><span class="cr-no">2</span><span class="cr-label">Not just dots</span
        ></a
      >
      <a href="#ch-toybox" data-ch="ch-toybox"
        ><span class="cr-no">3</span><span class="cr-label">Toy box</span></a
      >
    </nav>

    <!-- 1 · The invisible magnets -->
    <div class="chapter" id="ch-magnets">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="chapter-no">1</span>
        <h2 class="chapter-title">The invisible magnets</h2>
        <p class="chapter-sub">
          Drop a magnet on the page and watch the little dots react. Drag any of
          them around — the pull or push follows the word, not your cursor.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="concept reverse" data-form="wells">
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no"
            ><i class="fg fg-attract" style="--fc:#4da3ff"></i>Come here!</span
          >
          <h2>A word can call the dots in.</h2>
          <p>
            An <strong>attractor</strong> says “come here!” and the floating dots
            all swim toward it. The pull is tied to the word — drag it across the
            field and the dots chase it.
          </p>
          <p class="note">Give it a poke and watch the dots rush back in.</p>
          <button class="agitate" data-agitate="#m-attract">↯ Poke the field</button
          >
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">come here — drag me</span>
          <span
            class="body-chip"
            id="m-attract"
            data-drag
            data-body="attract"
            data-strength="1"
            data-range="300"
            style="--cc:#4da3ff; position:absolute; left:50%; top:50%; transform:translate(-50%,-50%);"
            ><i class="fg fg-attract"></i>come here</span
          >
          <span class="hintline">the dots swim toward it</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="concept" data-form="scatter">
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no"
            ><i class="fg fg-repel" style="--fc:#ff9d5c"></i>Stay back!</span
          >
          <h2>Or push them all away.</h2>
          <p>
            A <strong>repeller</strong> says “stay back!” — it carves out a clean
            space and the dots flow around it instead of through it.
          </p>
          <p class="note">Drag it into the crowd and watch a clearing open.</p>
          <button class="agitate" data-agitate="#m-repel">↯ Poke the field</button>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">stay back — drag me</span>
          <span
            class="body-chip"
            id="m-repel"
            data-drag
            data-body="repel"
            data-strength="1.1"
            data-range="300"
            style="--cc:#ff9d5c; position:absolute; left:50%; top:50%; transform:translate(-50%,-50%);"
            ><i class="fg fg-repel"></i>stay back</span
          >
          <span class="hintline">a clearing opens around it</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="concept reverse" data-form="wells">
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no"
            ><i class="fg fg-swirl" style="--fc:#2dd4bf"></i>Spin them</span
          >
          <h2>Some things spin the dots in circles.</h2>
          <p>
            A <strong>swirl</strong> sends the dots wheeling around it like water
            going down a drain — but gently, so they orbit instead of falling in.
          </p>
          <p class="note">Drag it through the swarm and stir.</p>
          <button class="agitate" data-agitate="#m-swirl">↯ Poke the field</button>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">spin — drag me</span>
          <span
            class="body-chip"
            id="m-swirl"
            data-drag
            data-body="swirl"
            data-spin="1"
            data-strength="1"
            data-range="320"
            style="--cc:#2dd4bf; position:absolute; left:50%; top:50%; transform:translate(-50%,-50%);"
            ><i class="fg fg-swirl"></i>spin</span
          >
          <span class="hintline">the dots wheel around, never collapse</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="concept" data-form="accretion">
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no"
            ><i class="fg fg-sink" style="--fc:#ff6e9c"></i>Gobble them</span
          >
          <h2>Some gobble them up like a tiny black hole.</h2>
          <p>
            A <strong>sink</strong> swallows the dots that wander too close —
            holding them at its core, not deleting them. Nothing is conjured from
            nothing; matter just changes hands.
          </p>
          <p class="note">Poke the field and feed it.</p>
          <button class="agitate" data-agitate="#m-sink">↯ Feed it</button>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">gobble — drag me</span>
          <span
            class="body-chip"
            id="m-sink"
            data-drag
            data-body="sink attract"
            data-absorb="64"
            data-max="14"
            data-strength="0.9"
            data-range="240"
            style="--cc:#ff6e9c; position:absolute; left:50%; top:50%; transform:translate(-50%,-50%);"
            ><i class="fg fg-sink"></i>gobble</span
          >
          <span class="hintline">dots get held at the core</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="concept reverse">
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no">✨ Both ways</span>
          <h2>And here’s the magic — it goes both ways.</h2>
          <p>
            The word pulls the dots in… and when lots of dots pile up, the word
            <strong>notices</strong>. It gets heavier, bolder, and glowier. The
            dots push the word, the word pushes back — they play together,
            forever. That’s the whole idea.
          </p>
          <p class="note">Hover the word — pull the dots in and watch it grow.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">pile up → it grows</span>
          <span
            class="live-demo"
            data-hot
            data-color="#a78bfa"
            data-feedback
            data-body="attract"
            data-strength="1"
            data-range="300"
            style="--cat:#a78bfa;">notice me</span
          >
          <span class="hintline">gathered dots make the word heavier</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 2 · When it's not just dots -->
    <div class="chapter" id="ch-things">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="chapter-no">2</span>
        <h2 class="chapter-title">When it’s not just dots</h2>
        <p class="chapter-sub">
          Here’s the secret: the dots were never the point. The field doesn’t care
          what you drop into it — the real words, the lines between them, even
          where you’re looking can all play.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="concept" data-form="wells">
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no">🟦 Words &amp; boxes</span>
          <h2>The headline itself becomes a magnet.</h2>
          <p>
            Drop in the actual words on the page and the headline gets heavy,
            glows, and the paragraph next to it leans away to make room. The page
            isn’t <em>decorated</em> by the field — the page <strong>lives
            inside</strong> it.
          </p>
          <p class="note">Hover the word to give it weight.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">a word with weight</span>
          <span
            class="live-demo"
            data-hot
            data-color="#7dd3fc"
            data-feedback
            data-body="attract"
            data-strength="1.1"
            data-range="300"
            style="--cat:#7dd3fc;">headline</span
          >
          <span class="hintline">heavy, glowing, alive</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="concept reverse">
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no">🔗 Lines between things</span>
          <h2>Related things tie themselves together.</h2>
          <p>
            A footnote and the sentence it belongs to are joined by an invisible
            rubber band — tug one and the other tugs back. Related things pull
            together; things that argue push apart. The connections become real,
            physical, grabbable.
          </p>
          <p class="note">Hover any word to light up its set.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">a connected set</span>
          <div class="thread-set" data-index data-threads>
            <span
              class="ti"
              data-hot
              data-color="#4da3ff"
              data-body="attract"
              data-strength="0.5"
              data-range="220"
              style="--cat:#4da3ff;">claim</span
            >
            <span
              class="ti"
              data-hot
              data-color="#2dd4bf"
              data-body="attract"
              data-strength="0.5"
              data-range="220"
              style="--cat:#2dd4bf;">proof</span
            >
            <span
              class="ti"
              data-hot
              data-color="#a78bfa"
              data-body="attract"
              data-strength="0.5"
              data-range="220"
              style="--cat:#a78bfa;">source</span
            >
            <span
              class="ti"
              data-hot
              data-color="#ff9d5c"
              data-body="attract"
              data-strength="0.5"
              data-range="220"
              style="--cat:#ff9d5c;">footnote</span
            >
          </div>
          <span class="hintline">threads connect what belongs together</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="concept" data-attention-demo>
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no">👀 Where you’re looking</span>
          <h2>The page knows you’re here.</h2>
          <p>
            As you scroll, the part you’re reading lights up like a flashlight
            beam — and the page remembers where you’ve already been, so those
            spots stay a little warm, like footprints in sand. A long article
            suddenly knows “you are here, you’ve read this.”
          </p>
          <p class="note">
            There’s only one spotlight of focus — hover one word and the others
            politely dim. Nothing screams for attention all at once.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">one spotlight, shared</span>
          <div class="attn-set">
            <span
              class="attn-word"
              data-hot
              data-feedback
              data-body="attract"
              data-strength="1.5"
              data-range="240"
              data-color="#4da3ff"
              style="--cat:#4da3ff;">here</span
            >
            <span
              class="attn-word"
              data-hot
              data-feedback
              data-body="attract"
              data-strength="1.5"
              data-range="240"
              data-color="#2dd4bf"
              style="--cat:#2dd4bf;">now</span
            >
            <span
              class="attn-word"
              data-hot
              data-feedback
              data-body="attract"
              data-strength="1.5"
              data-range="240"
              data-color="#ff9d5c"
              style="--cat:#ff9d5c;">read</span
            >
          </div>
          <span class="hintline">engage one — the others give up their glow</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="concept reverse" data-form="wells">
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no">📊 Data you can trust</span>
          <h2>Feel which answer to trust.</h2>
          <p>
            Drop in a pile of search results or a to-do list and each one becomes
            its own magnet. The important ones sink into a deep well and pull your
            eye; the shaky, unsure ones wobble; the ones with proof behind them
            sit solid and calm. You can feel which answer to trust before you even
            read it.
          </p>
          <p class="note">Poke it — the solid one barely flinches.</p>
          <button class="agitate" data-agitate="#m-trust">↯ Poke the field</button>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">important → deep well</span>
          <span
            class="body-chip"
            id="m-trust"
            data-drag
            data-body="attract"
            data-strength="1.4"
            data-range="300"
            style="--cc:#86e57f; position:absolute; left:50%; top:50%; transform:translate(-50%,-50%);"
            ><i class="fg fg-attract"></i>trusted</span
          >
          <span class="hintline">proof sits solid; doubt drifts</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="concept big-idea">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="bigidea-kicker">The big idea</p>
        <h2>
          Dots show you the field is there. <span class="accent"
            >Everything else is what the field is for.</span
          >
        </h2>
        <p>
          It’s not “a webpage with floating dots.” It’s a webpage where meaning has
          weight — where being important, being related, being trusted, or being
          already-read are things you can <strong>see and feel</strong>, not just
          words someone typed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 3 · The toy box -->
    <div class="chapter" id="ch-toybox">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="chapter-no">3</span>
        <h2 class="chapter-title">The toy box</h2>
        <p class="chapter-sub">
          Different games you can play with the same invisible field. They’re all
          the same magnets underneath — a new idea is just a new way to mix them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="concept">
      <div class="wrap">
        <ul class="toybox-grid">
          <li class="toy-card">
            <span class="toy-emoji" aria-hidden="true">✍️</span>
            <h3>Make words feel alive</h3>
            <p>One headline gets heavier, wider, warmer and glowier as it matters
              — and melts back to calm when it doesn’t. The type breathes.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="toy-card">
            <span class="toy-emoji" aria-hidden="true">🎯</span>
            <h3>Share one bucket of attention</h3>
            <p>One spotlight of focus for the whole page. Shine it here and the
              rest politely dim. Calm on purpose.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="toy-card">
            <span class="toy-emoji" aria-hidden="true">🧠</span>
            <h3>Give the page a memory</h3>
            <p>Where you’ve been stays warm. Spots you return to wear a path, like
              a trail through grass. The page learns your shape.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="toy-card">
            <span class="toy-emoji" aria-hidden="true">🤝</span>
            <h3>Help you trust answers</h3>
            <p>A claim with proof sits solid; a made-up one wobbles and drifts; two
              facts that argue push apart. Great for AI.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="toy-card">
            <span class="toy-emoji" aria-hidden="true">🌦️</span>
            <h3>Show a system’s “weather”</h3>
            <p>A dashboard of alerts can feel like a storm or a calm blue sky — “all
              fine” or “uh oh” in one glance, not 50 little red dots.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="toy-card">
            <span class="toy-emoji" aria-hidden="true">🧲</span>
            <h3>Let things arrange themselves</h3>
            <p>Boxes find their own comfy spots — pulled by what they belong to,
              pushed apart so they don’t crowd — and re-settle when the window
              changes.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="toy-card">
            <span class="toy-emoji" aria-hidden="true">🔍</span>
            <h3>Ask “why?”</h3>
            <p>Click anything and the page shows its work: “I moved because of THIS
              pull; I glow because of THESE friends nearby.” No mystery box.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="toy-card">
            <span class="toy-emoji" aria-hidden="true">♿</span>
            <h3>Works with the wiggle off</h3>
            <p>If motion makes someone dizzy, everything freezes but still means
              the same thing — the glow, the weight, the trail all stay.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="concept reverse">
      <div class="wrap concept-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="concept-no"
            ><i class="fgp fgp-blackhole"></i>🌌 Or just make something beautiful</span
          >
          <h2>Type <code>blackhole</code> and watch a universe form.</h2>
          <p>
            The same little pieces swirl into whole tiny universes — try
            <code>blackhole</code>, <code>galaxy</code>, <code>tornado</code>,
            <code>fountain</code>. A preset is just a bundle of magnets given a
            name.
          </p>
          <p class="note">Drag it around and let it pull the field into shape.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <span class="stage-label">blackhole — drag me</span>
          <span
            class="body-chip"
            data-drag
            data-preset="blackhole"
            style="--cc:#fbbf24; position:absolute; left:50%; top:50%; transform:translate(-50%,-50%);"
            ><i class="fgp fgp-blackhole"></i>blackhole</span
          >
          <span class="hintline">a whole little universe from a few magnets</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="manual-foot">
      <div class="wrap">
        <h2>New idea = mix the magnets a new way.</h2>
        <p class="foot-sub">
          A story, a dashboard, a game — they’re all the same field underneath.
          What do you want to make?
        </p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/lab">Open the Lab →</a>
          <a class="btn" href="/docs">Read the docs →</a>
          <a class="btn" href="/">See the grown-up version →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
  <SiteFooter />
</Base>

<!-- Page orchestrator — reuses the home interaction runtime + field-line overlay (both scan the
     document for .stage / [data-body] / [data-drag] / [data-threads] / [data-attention-demo] etc.,
     so this page behaves exactly like the main home). Tears down on navigation so nothing leaks. -->
<script>
  import { initHomeRuntime } from "../components/home/HomeRuntime.ts";
  import { initStageFieldOverlay } from "../components/home/StageFieldOverlay.ts";

  let teardownRuntime: (() => void) | undefined;
  let teardownOverlay: (() => void) | undefined;

  function teardown() {
    teardownRuntime?.();
    teardownOverlay?.();
    teardownRuntime = undefined;
    teardownOverlay = undefined;
  }

  function init() {
    teardown(); // idempotent: drop any prior run before re-wiring
    if (!document.querySelector(".manual-shell")) return;
    teardownRuntime = initHomeRuntime();
    teardownOverlay = initStageFieldOverlay();
  }

  if (document.readyState !== "loading") init();
  else document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", init);
  document.addEventListener("astro:page-load", init);
  document.addEventListener("astro:before-swap", teardown);
</script>

<style is:global>
  .stage {
    position: relative;
  }
  .stage-field {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
    opacity: 1;
    transition: opacity 0.25s ease;
  }
  .stage-field ~ * {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  html.hide-field-lines .stage-field {
    opacity: 0;
  }

  /* hero flow toggle — drives field.flowTo() */
  .hero-flow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .flow-toggle {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font: inherit;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: inherit;
    border: 1px solid var(--line, #2a2a35);
    background: transparent;
    transition:
      border-color 0.2s,
      background 0.2s;
  }
  .flow-toggle .ft-dot {
    width: 9px;
    height: 9px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #4da3ff;
    opacity: 0.5;
    transition:
      opacity 0.2s,
      box-shadow 0.2s;
  }
  .flow-toggle.on {
    border-color: #4da3ff;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #4da3ff 16%, transparent);
  }
  .flow-toggle.on .ft-dot {
    opacity: 1;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px 2px color-mix(in srgb, #4da3ff 70%, transparent);
  }
  .flow-hint {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--muted, #9aa);
  }
  .flow-hint code {
    font-size: 0.92em;
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .flow-toggle .ft-dot {
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>

<style>
  /* The "big idea" interstitial — a calm, centered beat between the two halves. */
  .big-idea .wrap {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 46rem;
  }
  .bigidea-kicker {
    font-family: var(--mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted, #9aa);
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .big-idea h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.4vw, 2.6rem);
    line-height: 1.12;
    margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
  }

  /* The toy box — a compact card grid, lighter than the full demo stages. */
